WEBVTT

00:02.378 --> 00:04.046
Michaela:
No one can explain

00:04.088 --> 00:06.799
what happened to us
on April 7, 2013.

00:06.841 --> 00:08.926
Some people
called it impossible.

00:08.968 --> 00:10.928
Others called it a miracle.

00:10.970 --> 00:15.516
All I know is...it was the day
my life changed forever.

00:15.558 --> 00:17.143
If you'd seen us
that afternoon,

00:17.184 --> 00:19.061
you probably would have thought
we looked like

00:19.103 --> 00:22.064
a typical American family
returning home from vacation.

00:22.106 --> 00:24.442
My brother, Ben,
and his wife, Grace,

00:24.483 --> 00:27.653
still in love after 15 years.

00:27.695 --> 00:29.697
Their twins, Olive and Cal,

00:29.739 --> 00:31.907
always bickering
like an old married couple.

00:31.949 --> 00:35.369
And the real old married
couple -- my parents.

00:35.411 --> 00:38.622
Still in perfect health,
still trying to run my life.

00:38.664 --> 00:41.459
It's not just
about you.

00:41.500 --> 00:44.253
This family needs
something to celebrate.

00:44.295 --> 00:47.715
Okay, that's a pretty backwards
reason for a wedding, but...

00:47.757 --> 00:49.425
Steve: How's this
for a reason?

00:49.467 --> 00:51.177
Jared loves you.

00:51.218 --> 00:52.636
And I know you love him.

00:52.678 --> 00:54.388
Typical, right?

00:54.430 --> 00:57.057
But what you couldn't see
is that Cal's leukemia

00:57.099 --> 00:58.934
wasn't responding
to treatment...

00:58.976 --> 01:00.853
or that Ben and Grace

01:00.895 --> 01:03.397
were desperately struggling
to find a cure...

01:03.439 --> 01:06.066
or that I still had nightmares
about the car accident.

01:06.108 --> 01:09.153
Michaela Beth, even people
that have made mistakes

01:09.195 --> 01:10.321
deserve happiness.

01:10.362 --> 01:11.489
[ Scoffs ]

01:11.530 --> 01:14.241
You know
my favorite verse --

01:14.283 --> 01:15.910
"All things work together
for good."

01:15.951 --> 01:19.538
I don't believe that anymore,
Mom. How can I?

01:19.580 --> 01:21.916
Which is why, when I got the
chance to stay away from home

01:21.957 --> 01:24.376
for even a few more hours,
I jumped at it.

01:24.418 --> 01:26.337
Woman: All passengers
for Flight 537 to New York,

01:26.378 --> 01:28.589
John F. Kennedy Airport,
your attention, please.

01:28.631 --> 01:30.424
This flight is oversold.

01:30.466 --> 01:33.344
We are offering travel vouchers
in the amount of $400

01:33.385 --> 01:35.596
for anyone willing
to take a later flight.

01:35.638 --> 01:38.224
Yes. That's me.

01:38.265 --> 01:39.850
-No.
-It's $400 per person.

01:39.892 --> 01:41.519
That's our next trip
down to the Mayo Clinic.

01:41.560 --> 01:42.978
I'll stay with Dad.

01:43.020 --> 01:45.481
There you go.
Man time.

01:45.523 --> 01:47.733
Ben:
All right. All right.

01:47.775 --> 01:50.152
So Grace and Olive and my folks

01:50.194 --> 01:52.279
took the first flight home

01:52.321 --> 01:55.991
while Ben and Cal and I
waited for Flight 828.

01:56.033 --> 01:59.203
♪♪

01:59.245 --> 02:02.915
Funny how one little decision
can ruin your life.

02:02.957 --> 02:05.417
But also save it.

02:09.046 --> 02:10.214
[ Keyboard keys clacking ]

02:10.256 --> 02:12.091
[ Cabin bell dings ]

02:12.132 --> 02:14.426
Peanuts?
You're welcome.

02:14.468 --> 02:17.596
Ma'am, would you
like peanuts?

02:17.638 --> 02:20.057
Do you have anything
sodium-free?

02:20.099 --> 02:21.684
Peanuts?

02:21.725 --> 02:25.020
[ Indistinct conversations ]

02:25.062 --> 02:27.106
Mom's not wrong. Jared's not
gonna wait around forever.

02:27.147 --> 02:29.233
Great marriage pep talk.
Thank you.

02:29.275 --> 02:31.902
Why are you fighting
this when all it's gonna
do is make you happy?

02:31.944 --> 02:33.654
It's all we want
for you.

02:33.696 --> 02:36.198
That was really sweet of you.
You must be drunk.

02:36.240 --> 02:38.158
Definitely.
[ Chuckles ]

02:40.995 --> 02:42.580
Say yes to Jared.

02:42.621 --> 02:46.625
Have a wedding and a honeymoon.
Turn the page. It's time.

02:46.667 --> 02:49.962
And, yes,
you deserve it.

02:53.090 --> 02:55.092
Truly.

02:55.134 --> 02:58.095
[ Thunder crashes ]

02:58.137 --> 03:00.306
[ Alarm blaring ]

03:00.347 --> 03:02.349
[ Passengers shouting ]

03:02.391 --> 03:03.601
It's okay. Everyone --

03:03.642 --> 03:05.311
[ Thunder crashes ]

03:05.352 --> 03:08.063
[ Banging ]

03:08.105 --> 03:10.816
[ Blaring continues ]

03:10.858 --> 03:13.777
[ Thunder crashes ]

03:13.819 --> 03:15.112
[ Passengers screaming ]

03:15.154 --> 03:18.073
[ Engines whining ]

03:24.580 --> 03:27.374
[ Cabin bell dings ]

03:27.416 --> 03:30.085
Daly: Ugh.
Terribly sorry, folks.

03:30.127 --> 03:31.837
That was extreme turbulence

03:31.879 --> 03:33.756
resulting from
a sudden weather surge

03:33.797 --> 03:35.591
that was not on the radar.

03:35.633 --> 03:38.135
Rest assured,
engines' controls are okay.

03:38.177 --> 03:40.888
But, please, keep
those seat belts fastened.

03:40.930 --> 03:44.099
Is there anything
crazy-important on there?

03:44.141 --> 03:46.852
Only six weeks' worth
of research data.

03:46.894 --> 03:48.145
Stewardess.

03:48.187 --> 03:49.688
I'm gonna need
another drink.

03:49.730 --> 03:53.233
You and me both, sir.
You and me both.

03:54.485 --> 03:56.153
Daly:
New York approach.

03:56.195 --> 03:59.740
Montego Air 8-2-8.
Level one five thousand.

03:59.782 --> 04:01.784
Man: This is
New York approach.

04:01.825 --> 04:03.953
Uh, repeat your
call sign, please?

04:03.994 --> 04:06.038
We are MA 8-2-8.

04:06.080 --> 04:08.040
[ Switch clicks, beep ]

04:10.584 --> 04:13.963
Repeat --
Montego Air 8-2-8.

04:14.004 --> 04:17.633
Montego Bay to JFK.
Copy that?

04:17.675 --> 04:21.095
Clarke: [ Jamaican accent ]
Any time now.

04:21.136 --> 04:23.222
Can I get your name, Captain,

04:23.263 --> 04:26.225
and the number of passengers
and crew on your manifest?

04:26.266 --> 04:29.436
Uh, this is
Captain William Daly.

04:29.478 --> 04:32.690
We have
191 souls on board,

04:32.731 --> 04:35.985
all of whom would love to touch
down on one of your runways.

04:37.194 --> 04:38.779
[ Cabin bell dings ]

04:38.821 --> 04:40.489
Daly: Sorry, folks.
Apologies and a half.

04:40.531 --> 04:42.741
We are diverting
to Stewart Airport

04:42.783 --> 04:44.451
up in Newburgh...
[ Passengers groan ]

04:44.493 --> 04:46.078
...spitting distance
from the city.

04:46.120 --> 04:48.122
But for any of those
who are trying to make

04:48.163 --> 04:50.207
a connecting flight,
we owe you one.

04:50.249 --> 04:52.209
Flight attendants,
prepare for landing.

04:52.251 --> 04:54.920
[ Cabin bell dings ]

04:54.962 --> 04:57.006
[ Engines roaring ]

05:00.634 --> 05:02.219
[ Tires screeching ]

05:02.261 --> 05:05.681
[ Scattered applause ]

05:05.723 --> 05:07.641
[ Cabin bell dings ]
Yes, we did, people.

05:07.683 --> 05:11.395
Welcome to New York,
where local time is 11:49 p.m.

05:11.437 --> 05:13.147
On behalf of your flight crew,

05:13.188 --> 05:16.025
we'd like to thank you all
for flying Montego Air.

05:16.066 --> 05:17.693
Seriously?
No service?

05:17.735 --> 05:19.361
Same.
[ Cabin bell dings ]

05:19.403 --> 05:21.905
Daly: And the
inconvenience continues.

05:21.947 --> 05:24.908
We've been asked to deplane
right here on the tarmac.

05:24.950 --> 05:26.160
Cool!

05:26.201 --> 05:28.954
[ Sirens wailing ]

05:34.877 --> 05:38.714
[ Police radio chatter ]

05:38.756 --> 05:40.799
[ Sirens stop ]

05:40.841 --> 05:42.134
[ Indistinct conversations ]

05:42.176 --> 05:43.927
[ Police radio chatter ]

05:43.969 --> 05:46.555
♪♪

05:46.597 --> 05:48.098
Who's Daly?

05:48.140 --> 05:50.142
When do they
ever do this?

05:50.184 --> 05:53.353
Never.
Something's happening.

05:53.395 --> 05:55.647
♪♪

05:55.689 --> 05:57.149
[ Police radio chatter ]

05:57.191 --> 05:58.984
Michaela: Excuse me.
T-There are sick people here.

05:59.026 --> 06:01.111
What exactly
is the problem?

06:01.153 --> 06:03.655
♪♪

06:03.697 --> 06:05.449
The problem,
ladies and gentlemen,

06:05.491 --> 06:08.327
is your plane departed
Montego Bay, Jamaica,

06:08.368 --> 06:11.538
on April 7, 2013.

06:12.581 --> 06:17.503
Today is November 4, 2018.

06:17.544 --> 06:19.171
[ Passengers murmuring ]

06:19.213 --> 06:23.175
You've all been missing,
presumed dead, for 5 1/2 years.

06:23.217 --> 06:26.220
What?!
[ Passengers murmuring ]

06:26.261 --> 06:27.888
♪♪

06:27.930 --> 06:30.891
[ Engines roaring ]

06:30.933 --> 06:34.812
♪♪

06:34.853 --> 06:36.647
[ Radio chatter ]

06:36.688 --> 06:45.447
♪♪

06:45.489 --> 06:46.949
-Hey.
-Hm?

06:46.990 --> 06:49.326
Medicine.

06:49.368 --> 06:52.454
♪♪

06:52.496 --> 06:54.248
When can we leave?

06:54.289 --> 06:55.833
[ Pills rattle ]

06:57.209 --> 06:59.211
Soon, buddy.
They're just --

06:59.253 --> 07:01.213
They're gonna talk to us,
take a little look at us,

07:01.255 --> 07:03.340
and then we can
get out of here, okay?

07:03.382 --> 07:06.510
♪♪

07:06.552 --> 07:09.096
If it's really been
five years,

07:09.138 --> 07:11.390
how am I still alive?

07:11.431 --> 07:15.644
♪♪

07:15.686 --> 07:18.772
Do you feel
five years older?

07:18.814 --> 07:20.566
Neither do I.

07:21.817 --> 07:22.943
Don't worry.

07:22.985 --> 07:29.950
♪♪

07:29.992 --> 07:31.743
Vance:
Let's start simply.

07:31.785 --> 07:34.163
After the plane left Jamaica,
where did you land?

07:35.205 --> 07:37.749
We never landed anywhere
until we landed right here.

07:37.791 --> 07:39.501
Now tell me what
really happened.

07:39.543 --> 07:43.172
Took off on time. Arrived
3 hours and 19 minutes later.

07:43.213 --> 07:46.008
Is this some kind of a stunt?!
For God's sake!

07:46.049 --> 07:47.676
It makes no sense.

07:47.718 --> 07:49.469
Clear air, heavy chop.

07:49.511 --> 07:51.471
Instruments never detected
a thing.

07:51.513 --> 07:53.265
Turbulence.

07:53.307 --> 07:56.476
Like the roof was going to
come right off, you know?

07:56.518 --> 07:59.396
[ Sobbing ] I...
We...

07:59.438 --> 08:02.608
What are you talking --

08:02.649 --> 08:05.444
I'm gonna sue this airline
into the ground.

08:05.485 --> 08:06.945
I need to make a call, okay?

08:06.987 --> 08:09.781
I need -- I need to
call my boy-- my fiancé.

08:09.823 --> 08:11.408
My son has leukemia.

08:11.450 --> 08:13.952
He's not about to submit
to testing of any kind.

08:15.245 --> 08:17.873
I want my mom.

08:17.915 --> 08:20.500
[ Indistinct shouting ]

08:20.542 --> 08:26.673
♪♪

08:26.715 --> 08:28.508
Grace: Ben!

08:28.550 --> 08:30.969
Ben! Ben!
Oh, my God!

08:31.011 --> 08:34.014
♪♪

08:34.056 --> 08:36.058
Steve: Ohh!

08:36.099 --> 08:37.726
It's okay.
We're okay.

08:37.768 --> 08:39.353
-[ Laughs ]
-We're okay.

08:39.394 --> 08:42.272
I don't understand.
How are you exactly the same?

08:42.314 --> 08:44.399
You...haven't aged a day.

08:44.441 --> 08:46.068
[ Sobs ]

08:46.109 --> 08:54.618
♪♪

08:54.660 --> 08:56.578
Olive.

08:56.620 --> 09:02.626
♪♪

09:02.668 --> 09:08.674
♪♪

09:08.715 --> 09:10.509
Cal! Cal!

09:10.550 --> 09:12.803
Cal! Cal, Cal.

09:12.844 --> 09:16.223
I know, I know, I know.
It's okay.

09:16.265 --> 09:18.892
Where's, uh --
Where's mom and Jared?

09:18.934 --> 09:21.061
I texted with Jared.

09:21.103 --> 09:24.439
He couldn't make it over.
Work emergency.

09:25.524 --> 09:27.109
And Mom?

09:30.112 --> 09:31.530
Your mom got sick.

09:31.571 --> 09:34.032
She -- She fought so hard.

09:34.074 --> 09:35.826
What do you --
What do you mean, sick?

09:35.867 --> 09:37.953
[ Sighs ]

09:37.995 --> 09:40.539
She loved you kids
more than life itself.

09:40.580 --> 09:42.749
You were everything to her.
-No! No, no.

09:42.791 --> 09:45.168
I was just -- I was just running
with her on the beach.

09:45.210 --> 09:47.296
I came out here
to tell her

09:47.337 --> 09:49.256
t-that she was right
about me and Jared.

09:49.298 --> 09:50.882
[ Sobbing ]
No, Dad. No, no!

09:50.924 --> 09:52.884
No, I can't --

09:52.926 --> 09:55.387
[ Sobbing ]

09:55.429 --> 10:01.018
♪♪

10:01.059 --> 10:06.648
♪♪

10:06.690 --> 10:08.900
Woman: ...as the entire world
focuses on Flight 828.

10:08.942 --> 10:10.444
Man: Where was Flight 828
for five years?

10:10.485 --> 10:12.529
Woman: As a multitude
of government agencies,

10:12.571 --> 10:15.449
including NASA,
Homeland Security, and the NSA,

10:15.490 --> 10:17.951
descend upon New York,
the story of the century

10:17.993 --> 10:20.329
now touches this
middle-class neighborhood

10:20.370 --> 10:22.789
here in suburban Queens.

10:22.831 --> 10:31.673
♪♪

10:31.715 --> 10:40.557
♪♪

10:40.599 --> 10:49.441
♪♪

10:49.483 --> 10:58.325
♪♪

10:58.367 --> 11:01.995
Grace: Your mom
made it after...

11:02.037 --> 11:04.289
That cheesy verse
was her mantra.

11:04.331 --> 11:06.291
[ Chuckles ]

11:08.126 --> 11:10.545
Actually, I'm pretty sure it's
the last thing she said to me.

11:12.714 --> 11:15.050
I'm sorry to
stick you down here.

11:15.092 --> 11:17.344
We hung onto your apartment
as long as we could,

11:17.386 --> 11:19.513
but eventually,
we had to let it go.

11:22.015 --> 11:23.433
Hey, can I
use the phone?

11:23.475 --> 11:25.394
Yeah, of course.

11:25.435 --> 11:26.853
[ Cellphone unlocks ]
Thanks.

11:26.895 --> 11:29.189
We gave up the landline.

11:35.570 --> 11:37.197
[ Ringing ]

11:37.239 --> 11:39.533
Hey, it's Jared Vasquez.
Please leave a mess--

11:43.662 --> 11:45.038
All set.

11:45.080 --> 11:46.415
Thank you.

11:48.125 --> 11:50.585
Hey, Grace?

11:50.627 --> 11:53.713
Look, I know you probably don't
want, uh, Miss Bad Influence

11:53.755 --> 11:55.048
hanging around the kids.

11:55.090 --> 11:56.550
I would get --
Michaela, no.

11:56.591 --> 11:59.970
M-Michaela...
this is your home.

12:00.011 --> 12:02.347
For as long as you'd like.

12:02.389 --> 12:03.598
That's ancient history.

12:03.640 --> 12:05.475
It was two days ago
for me.

12:05.517 --> 12:07.394
I am still
the same screw-up

12:07.436 --> 12:09.187
that you said goodbye to
in Jamaica.

12:09.229 --> 12:13.066
The universe just gave all of us
a do-over.

12:13.108 --> 12:17.279
Everything that happened before
goes out the window.

12:20.407 --> 12:22.617
Michaela: [ Echoing ]
All things...

12:24.119 --> 12:26.746
Are you okay?

12:26.788 --> 12:29.708
Yeah. Yeah, I'm okay.
Sorry.

12:29.749 --> 12:32.210
[ Chuckles ] Okay.

12:32.252 --> 12:33.670
Anything you need, please.

12:33.712 --> 12:35.172
I'm just upstairs.
-Okay. Thanks.

12:35.213 --> 12:43.472
♪♪

12:43.513 --> 12:51.730
♪♪

12:51.771 --> 12:54.232
[ Instrument warbling ]

12:54.274 --> 13:01.281
♪♪

13:01.323 --> 13:03.325
[ Beeping ]

13:03.366 --> 13:09.748
♪♪

13:09.789 --> 13:12.542
We interviewed every
last one of them. Nothing.

13:12.584 --> 13:14.753
And still haven't come across
a single substance

13:14.794 --> 13:17.589
dating from any time between
the day the flight took off

13:17.631 --> 13:18.924
and when it returned.

13:18.965 --> 13:20.675
It's as if the plane
never left the sky.

13:20.717 --> 13:23.428
Do I have to say out loud
that that's impossible?

13:23.470 --> 13:26.890
Director, no one on that plane
aged a day.

13:26.932 --> 13:30.435
I think we've taken impossible
off the table.

13:30.477 --> 13:33.063
♪♪

13:39.402 --> 13:41.404
[ Indistinct conversations ]

13:43.532 --> 13:45.534
[ Indistinct conversations ]

13:45.575 --> 13:47.661
[ Police radio chatter ]

13:52.123 --> 13:53.792
As I live and breathe.

13:53.833 --> 13:56.002
Hey, Sarge.

13:56.044 --> 13:58.380
Getting a lifetime supply
of hugs.

13:58.421 --> 13:59.923
Of course you are.

13:59.965 --> 14:02.926
Come back from the dead,
you've earned yourself a hug.

14:02.968 --> 14:05.929
Didn't expect you getting
back to work this fast.

14:05.971 --> 14:07.806
Probably not quite yet,

14:07.847 --> 14:09.975
assuming I actually
still have a job here.

14:10.016 --> 14:13.812
Technically, you still remain
on desk duty.

14:13.853 --> 14:17.148
I'm guessing we can drum up a
desk for you when you're ready.

14:17.190 --> 14:21.903
♪♪

14:21.945 --> 14:26.116
You're so young.
You look exactly the same.

14:26.157 --> 14:28.618
Yeah.

14:28.660 --> 14:32.372
You look even better.
I don't know how men do that.

14:34.583 --> 14:37.127
I'm sorry I didn't come
to the airport.

14:37.168 --> 14:39.546
I'm lead detective
on this abduction case.

14:39.588 --> 14:40.839
Every hour counts.

14:40.880 --> 14:42.841
Detective? Wow.

14:44.050 --> 14:47.304
A lot has changed
since you've been gone.

14:48.722 --> 14:56.354
♪♪

14:56.396 --> 14:58.440
Who is she?

14:58.481 --> 14:59.774
[ Sighs ]

15:01.943 --> 15:03.278
Lourdes.

15:06.239 --> 15:10.327
That makes sense. She always
told me how lucky I was.

15:10.368 --> 15:11.995
Michaela,
it was two years

15:12.037 --> 15:13.455
before I even looked
at another woman.

15:13.496 --> 15:15.707
Sorry. I, uh...

15:15.749 --> 15:19.836
♪♪

15:19.878 --> 15:21.921
[ Monitor beeping ]

15:25.967 --> 15:28.178
You okay?

15:29.512 --> 15:33.016
His cell count is exactly the
same. We're right where we were.

15:33.058 --> 15:35.935
It's amazing.
It's truly amazing.

15:35.977 --> 15:39.064
So we pick up with
the same regimen, right
where we left off?

15:39.105 --> 15:40.982
Well, that would be
our backup plan,

15:41.024 --> 15:43.276
but there's a new treatment
protocol for pediatric cases

15:43.318 --> 15:44.944
within Cal's profile.

15:44.986 --> 15:46.279
It's a game-changer.

15:46.321 --> 15:48.448
Game-changer how?

15:48.490 --> 15:50.158
Well, it's still in
the phase 3 trial,

15:50.200 --> 15:52.160
so we have to apply for him
to join the patient group,

15:52.202 --> 15:53.953
which I'll do right now.

15:53.995 --> 15:57.791
If we get him admitted and
we get a jump on the treatment,

15:57.832 --> 15:59.292
the odds are excellent.

15:59.334 --> 16:01.252
[ Exhales sharply ]

16:01.294 --> 16:04.297
Uh, can we manage
some expectations here?

16:04.339 --> 16:07.258
You said six months. You implied
it would take a miracle.

16:07.300 --> 16:08.760
Earth to Ben.

16:08.802 --> 16:10.720
You all came back to us.

16:10.762 --> 16:13.473
You are sitting here
right now, baby.

16:13.515 --> 16:15.975
[ Laughing ]
A miracle just happened!

16:16.017 --> 16:22.649
♪♪

16:22.691 --> 16:25.944
Woman: ...coverage of Montego
Air Flight 828 will continue,

16:25.985 --> 16:28.196
but first this NBC4 Update.

16:28.238 --> 16:31.324
Sisters Hallie and
Samantha Pyler of Astoria

16:31.366 --> 16:34.244
were abducted from their
backyard early Sunday morning.

16:34.285 --> 16:37.872
The case has resulted in
thousands of calls to the NYPD,

16:37.914 --> 16:41.751
according to 129th Precinct
Detective Jared Vasquez.

16:41.793 --> 16:44.212
We're working nonstop
pursuing all viable leads.

16:44.254 --> 16:45.880
Please keep
your eyes and ears open.

16:45.922 --> 16:47.465
If you hear anything,
make sure you contact

16:47.507 --> 16:48.925
your local police department.

16:58.935 --> 17:01.438
Michaela:
[ Echoing ] Slower.

17:02.605 --> 17:05.108
Slower!

17:10.071 --> 17:11.698
Excuse me.
Can you slow down?

17:13.867 --> 17:15.910
Excuse me?
-Do I come to your work

17:15.952 --> 17:18.121
and tell you
how to do your job?

17:22.292 --> 17:23.877
Slower!
[ Grunts ]

17:23.918 --> 17:25.712
Slow down! Now!

17:25.754 --> 17:27.839
[ Tires screeching ]

17:30.258 --> 17:34.345
How'd you see him coming?!
Lady! How the hell?!

17:34.387 --> 17:39.184
♪♪

17:39.225 --> 17:41.144
[ Door closes ]

17:41.186 --> 17:47.734
♪♪

17:47.776 --> 17:50.195
You all right?

17:50.236 --> 17:52.906
Is your mind
messing with you?

17:52.947 --> 17:55.241
[ Chuckles ]
Where to begin?

17:55.283 --> 17:56.785
Ben, I'm serious.

17:56.826 --> 17:59.537
Earlier today, I heard
a voice in my head.

18:01.915 --> 18:03.458
What do you mean, voice?
Whose voice?

18:03.500 --> 18:05.668
It was my voice,
but it was talking to me.

18:07.086 --> 18:09.380
So, like
a psychotic voice?

18:10.465 --> 18:12.592
Can you not diagnose me
right now and just listen?

18:14.302 --> 18:17.096
Look, normally I'd go
to Mom about all this,
but now I'm stuck with you.

18:17.138 --> 18:19.432
-I lost my mom, too.
-I didn't mean that.

18:19.474 --> 18:21.976
I know. Sorry.

18:22.018 --> 18:25.146
♪♪

18:25.188 --> 18:28.483
You want to know
what I think?

18:28.525 --> 18:30.652
I think it sounds like
you're losing your mind.

18:30.693 --> 18:33.154
[ Chuckles ]
Yeah, of course you do.

18:33.196 --> 18:35.156
No, I'm not being glib.

18:35.198 --> 18:37.200
Keep it to yourself before
you end up in a psych ward

18:37.242 --> 18:39.619
having exploratory
brain surgery.

18:39.661 --> 18:41.287
What do you think,
the government

18:41.329 --> 18:44.415
just sent us home
and forgot about us?

18:44.457 --> 18:46.251
Who knows what they'll try in
order to find out what happened?

18:46.292 --> 18:49.671
And I don't want anything
to happen to you.

18:51.297 --> 18:52.799
That's what I think.

18:55.802 --> 18:58.596
[ Horns honking,
indistinct conversations ]

19:00.682 --> 19:03.518
-Hold your horses, honey.
-What? What?!

19:03.560 --> 19:06.646
Oh, my. [ Chuckles ]
Really?

19:10.692 --> 19:12.777
[ Elevator bell dings ]

19:16.489 --> 19:18.867
All: Surprise!

19:18.908 --> 19:21.244
[ Cheers and applause ]

19:28.585 --> 19:32.255
-Saanvi?
-Dr. Cardoso. Hi.

19:32.297 --> 19:34.632
Look, I don't understand.
I was trying to race to you

19:34.674 --> 19:36.676
so I can get you my research
off of the portal, and --

19:36.718 --> 19:39.262
I got your research
five years ago.

19:39.304 --> 19:41.055
Your cell-regeneration model

19:41.097 --> 19:42.932
isn't just theoretical
after all.

19:42.974 --> 19:45.226
It works? As an actual
clinical success?

19:45.268 --> 19:47.145
We've been treating
pediatric cancer patients

19:47.186 --> 19:48.980
for close to 30 months.

19:49.022 --> 19:50.648
Oh, you can't be serious.

19:50.690 --> 19:54.068
Couldn't be more. It's already
saved hundreds of young lives.

19:54.110 --> 19:56.154
[ Chuckles ]

19:56.195 --> 19:57.405
Dad, can I have a pretzel?

19:57.447 --> 19:59.032
Pretzel?

19:59.073 --> 20:01.409
I guess.

20:01.451 --> 20:02.785
Here you go, buddy.
-Thanks.

20:02.827 --> 20:04.454
[ Horns honking ]

20:04.495 --> 20:05.747
I need a job.

20:05.788 --> 20:07.457
If we luck into
this treatment,

20:07.498 --> 20:09.083
chances are
it's gonna cost a fortune,

20:09.125 --> 20:10.752
and work insurance
won't pay for it.

20:10.793 --> 20:14.422
We don't know that.
It pays for Olive's therapy.

20:14.464 --> 20:15.882
She goes to therapy?

20:15.924 --> 20:18.134
Yeah. Twice a week.
For years now.

20:18.176 --> 20:21.304
Early on, she didn't even
want to leave the house,

20:21.346 --> 20:23.514
let alone ride in a car
or go to school.

20:23.556 --> 20:26.267
She couldn't have sleepovers
'cause of the nightmares.

20:26.309 --> 20:29.437
I mean, most of that's gone now,
thank God.

20:29.479 --> 20:30.897
She grew up too fast.

20:30.939 --> 20:33.775
She had no choice.

20:34.609 --> 20:41.157
♪♪

20:41.199 --> 20:47.789
♪♪

20:47.830 --> 20:50.083
[ Dogs barking ]

20:51.042 --> 20:53.211
[ Echoing ] Set them free!

20:53.252 --> 20:55.088
[ Barking continues ]

20:55.129 --> 20:57.090
Set them free!

20:57.131 --> 20:58.758
[ Barking continues ]

20:58.800 --> 21:01.177
♪♪

21:01.219 --> 21:02.637
Set them free.

21:02.679 --> 21:04.180
[ Barking continues ]

21:04.222 --> 21:07.392
♪♪

21:07.433 --> 21:10.269
[ Insects chirping ]

21:10.311 --> 21:12.605
Set them free.

21:14.232 --> 21:17.068
Set them free.

21:17.110 --> 21:18.319
Set them free.

21:18.361 --> 21:19.862
[ Breathing heavily ]

21:19.904 --> 21:22.198
Set them free!

21:22.240 --> 21:31.374
♪♪

21:31.416 --> 21:40.591
♪♪

21:40.633 --> 21:43.553
[ Dogs barking ]

21:50.018 --> 21:52.145
[ Barking continues ]

21:52.186 --> 21:54.939
[ Engine shuts off,
barking stops ]

21:58.735 --> 22:00.319
How'd you find me?

22:00.361 --> 22:03.197
[ Barking resumes ]

22:03.239 --> 22:05.366
Ben.

22:05.408 --> 22:07.618
What are you doing here?

22:09.328 --> 22:10.913
Setting them free.

22:12.665 --> 22:16.919
I've been hearing it ever since
I drove by here this afternoon.

22:16.961 --> 22:19.797
You said I was losing my mind,
Ben! Why'd you lie to me?

22:19.839 --> 22:23.342
Because maybe I don't want
to be a circus freak!

22:23.384 --> 22:24.886
I don't have
the time for it.

22:24.927 --> 22:27.388
I got to help Cal,
find a goddamn job,

22:27.430 --> 22:30.099
get to know my daughter,
reclaim my life!

22:30.141 --> 22:32.602
Do you think I am
any happier about this?

22:32.643 --> 22:36.189
Who would want to
reclaim my life, Ben?

22:36.230 --> 22:39.025
Part of me wishes we hadn't come
back at all, but here we are.

22:47.200 --> 22:49.285
[ Vehicle door closes ]

22:49.327 --> 22:52.163
To be clear,
this is a felony.

22:52.205 --> 22:53.581
Yeah, I'm a police officer.

22:53.623 --> 22:55.833
I'm pretty sure
I know what a felony is.

22:55.875 --> 22:57.919
[ Dogs barking ]

22:57.960 --> 23:00.004
Hey, what if
they attack us?

23:00.046 --> 23:01.839
They'd be doing
their job.

23:03.216 --> 23:04.926
[ Barking continues ]

23:09.013 --> 23:11.682
[ Barking stops ]

23:11.724 --> 23:19.398
♪♪

23:22.068 --> 23:24.862
♪♪

23:24.904 --> 23:26.447
That was bizarre.

23:26.489 --> 23:28.032
You think?

23:29.784 --> 23:31.119
Now what?

23:31.160 --> 23:33.579
I don't know.

23:33.621 --> 23:36.707
But hearing a voice in your head
one time is a fluke. Twice?

23:36.749 --> 23:40.044
Now happening
to the both of us?

23:40.086 --> 23:41.963
Not a fluke.

23:48.636 --> 23:50.012
Older lady marches in
this morning,

23:50.054 --> 23:51.681
says she witnessed a break-in
last night

23:51.722 --> 23:53.391
on a commercial property across
from her residence.

23:53.432 --> 23:55.393
Hell of a story.
You need me on this because...?

23:55.434 --> 23:56.727
She was
pretty resourceful.

23:56.769 --> 23:58.479
Recorded the whole thing
on her phone.

23:58.521 --> 23:59.772
[ Keyboard clacks ]

24:01.607 --> 24:03.693
They never enter the property,
just let the dogs out,

24:03.734 --> 24:06.529
which were picked up
by Animal Control this morning.

24:06.571 --> 24:09.031
Look, I could go ahead and
process the complaint, unless...

24:09.073 --> 24:10.908
you want to handle it.

24:13.578 --> 24:15.371
Jared:
Help me out here.

24:15.413 --> 24:17.331
Michaela, I got three detectives
and eight uniforms

24:17.373 --> 24:19.500
waiting on my direction
to find these abducted girls,

24:19.542 --> 24:22.503
and I'm here trying
to put out your fire.

24:22.545 --> 24:24.547
Does this
have to do with me?

24:24.589 --> 24:25.756
Excuse me. How?

24:25.798 --> 24:28.467
I don't know. All right?

24:28.509 --> 24:29.927
Acting out, you know,

24:29.969 --> 24:31.512
trying to get my attention,
get back at me.

24:31.554 --> 24:33.055
You are such a guy.

24:33.097 --> 24:34.640
I break open a fence,
and, yeah, it's because

24:34.682 --> 24:36.434
you've married
my best friend.

24:36.475 --> 24:39.770
Look, Lourdes is amazing.
You're both amazing.

24:39.812 --> 24:41.981
I was gone.

24:42.023 --> 24:44.901
How can I blame
either of you, right?

24:46.527 --> 24:47.820
Fine. Then what?

24:49.906 --> 24:52.450
What?

24:52.491 --> 24:54.327
Huh.

24:54.368 --> 24:56.245
I don't know.

24:56.287 --> 24:58.247
How about the fact that
I take off in a plane,

24:58.289 --> 25:00.458
and when I land,
my mom is dead?

25:00.499 --> 25:03.669
Thanks for your condolences,
by the way.

25:03.711 --> 25:06.547
How about the fact that I have
no home, no phone number,

25:06.589 --> 25:09.800
not a single worldly possession
at all to my name?

25:09.842 --> 25:14.055
How about that I lost 5 years,
6 months, and 28 days

25:14.096 --> 25:17.308
of the world, of life?

25:17.350 --> 25:19.644
How about -- Never mind
that my lawyer

25:19.685 --> 25:21.729
convinced a judge
that I was innocent.

25:21.771 --> 25:24.273
I will never, ever
stop believing that
I didn't commit murder

25:24.315 --> 25:26.817
when Evie died sitting
next to me in my car.

25:26.859 --> 25:29.195
So, yeah, as I am standing here,
I am trying to figure out

25:29.237 --> 25:32.114
whether or not I
should be grateful for
being back and alive

25:32.156 --> 25:35.243
or just guilty, Jared.

25:35.284 --> 25:37.119
Which is
where I'm leaning.

25:37.161 --> 25:41.624
♪♪

25:41.666 --> 25:43.834
[ Sobbing ]

25:43.876 --> 25:49.590
♪♪

25:49.632 --> 25:55.346
♪♪

25:55.388 --> 26:00.351
Michaela, I'm sorry
about your mother.

26:00.393 --> 26:04.438
I'm so sorry
about everything.

26:04.480 --> 26:06.565
I'm still trying to wrap my mind
around it all myself.

26:06.607 --> 26:09.777
Believe me.
But I still need an answer.

26:09.819 --> 26:13.239
Why? Why did you and your
brother break open that fence?

26:13.281 --> 26:16.951
I can't explain it.
I wish I could.

26:16.993 --> 26:18.619
Go inside and put
some more clothes on.

26:18.661 --> 26:20.329
-Why?
-'Cause you're coming with me

26:20.371 --> 26:23.291
to make this go away
and save your career.

26:23.332 --> 26:26.627
Please.

26:28.254 --> 26:31.549
[ Indistinct shouting ]

26:31.590 --> 26:33.301
Over here!

26:33.342 --> 26:35.428
Man: All right, both teams,
take a break!

26:35.469 --> 26:37.680
[ Indistinct shouting ]

26:37.722 --> 26:41.183
Man: Touch and go.
Touch and go.

26:41.225 --> 26:44.895
Dad.
What are you doing here?

26:44.937 --> 26:47.106
Checking out the team.
You guys look good.

26:47.148 --> 26:50.651
Thanks. Parents don't usually
show up to practice.

26:50.693 --> 26:54.613
Well, this parent's got
some catching up to do.

26:54.655 --> 26:58.075
Listen. I...

26:58.117 --> 27:02.663
just wanted to say
I'm so sorry for...

27:02.705 --> 27:04.415
everything.

27:04.457 --> 27:06.876
Dad, you don't
have to apologize

27:06.917 --> 27:09.086
for something
that happened to you.

27:09.128 --> 27:11.672
I made the choice
to stay behind.

27:11.714 --> 27:14.091
-It was a long time ago, Dad.
-Not for me.

27:14.133 --> 27:18.846
Here you've been all this time,
stuck, picking up the pieces.

27:20.848 --> 27:22.391
Even before
I got on that plane,

27:22.433 --> 27:28.105
I'd been so caught up with
trying to help Cal get better

27:28.147 --> 27:30.274
so he could live
a long life. I...

27:32.318 --> 27:34.195
I lost sight
of your life.

27:34.236 --> 27:37.114
♪♪

27:37.156 --> 27:42.161
And now you probably feel
like you don't know me.

27:42.203 --> 27:44.455
But we're gonna fix that.

27:44.497 --> 27:46.332
I'm not going anywhere.

27:46.374 --> 27:53.589
♪♪

27:53.631 --> 27:54.924
[ Whistle blows ]

27:54.965 --> 27:57.718
Hey, you better
get back out there.

27:57.760 --> 28:05.601
♪♪

28:05.643 --> 28:07.228
Dr. Miller: We have a full plate
today, so we'll just table

28:07.269 --> 28:08.938
the rest of the reports
until next week.

28:08.979 --> 28:10.356
Is that good?

28:10.398 --> 28:12.900
Moving on to new applicants.

28:12.942 --> 28:15.569
How often do these
reviews happen?

28:15.611 --> 28:17.446
Oh.
Almost every day.

28:17.488 --> 28:19.657
Your survival rates
are through the roof.

28:19.698 --> 28:21.659
Who wouldn't want in?

28:21.700 --> 28:24.578
Okay, here we go.

28:24.620 --> 28:26.747
This is an unusual case.

28:26.789 --> 28:30.376
Male born April 19, 2002.

28:30.418 --> 28:34.255
Initial diagnosis
was back in 2011.

28:34.296 --> 28:35.881
Excuse me?

28:35.923 --> 28:38.884
Treating narrative says
the boy was on Flight 828.

28:42.054 --> 28:45.516
Wow. Uh...

28:46.809 --> 28:49.603
Okay, uh, unfortunately,
his diagnosis date

28:49.645 --> 28:51.522
is outside
the study parameters.

28:51.564 --> 28:54.483
He's lived with this disease
for more than six years.

28:54.525 --> 28:57.528
No, excuse me. For him,
it hasn't been six years.

28:57.570 --> 28:59.405
Now, if this boy
needed treatment

28:59.447 --> 29:01.157
before he got
onto that plane,

29:01.198 --> 29:03.033
he undoubtedly
would need it now.

29:03.075 --> 29:06.036
Of course, I understand
how you feel, but...

29:06.078 --> 29:08.080
we can't risk
breaking protocol.

29:08.122 --> 29:12.835
I think we need to deny.
Are we in agreement?

29:12.877 --> 29:14.336
[ Indistinct murmuring ]

29:16.589 --> 29:18.090
[ Door opens ]

29:18.132 --> 29:20.634
[ Door closes ]

29:24.889 --> 29:26.432
[ Knock on door ]
Oh, there you are.

29:26.474 --> 29:28.976
I reviewed his profile.
He is all but terminal.

29:29.018 --> 29:30.811
Saanvi, we can't
save everyone.

29:30.853 --> 29:32.563
No, of course not,
but we can try.

29:32.605 --> 29:34.231
For the credibility
of the study,

29:34.273 --> 29:36.275
only the most viable cases
can be included.

29:36.317 --> 29:38.819
Says who? This is your study
based on my research.

29:38.861 --> 29:40.654
I'm entitled
to a voice here.

29:40.696 --> 29:43.365
We're months away
from being bought

29:43.407 --> 29:44.825
by a major pharmaceutical.

29:44.867 --> 29:46.785
There's too much money
on the line for both of us,

29:46.827 --> 29:48.370
and I won't let that
be jeopardized

29:48.412 --> 29:49.872
by an aberrant patient

29:49.914 --> 29:52.416
whose results might compromise
our track record.

29:52.458 --> 29:54.376
Who knows what happened to him
on that plane?

29:54.418 --> 29:57.004
Do you want to know what
happened to him on that plane?

29:57.046 --> 29:59.256
The exact same thing
that happened to me.

29:59.298 --> 30:01.133
We both got
a second chance.

30:01.175 --> 30:04.553
To start over, to live.

30:04.595 --> 30:08.057
And I can't explain to you
why or how,

30:08.098 --> 30:10.643
but I'm not ruling out that just
maybe he came back to be saved

30:10.684 --> 30:13.020
and I came back
to save him.

30:14.563 --> 30:16.482
And I couldn't care less
about the money.

30:16.524 --> 30:19.652
We're giving this boy
his chance.

30:19.693 --> 30:21.987
[ Dogs whining ]

30:22.029 --> 30:23.447
Come on.

30:23.489 --> 30:24.990
Is this really necessary?

30:25.032 --> 30:26.617
Yeah. Yeah.
You're doing this.

30:26.659 --> 30:28.786
I'm just along
for the ride.

30:28.827 --> 30:30.746
Let's just hope he doesn't
want to press charges.

30:30.788 --> 30:32.373
Michaela:
[ Echoing ] Set them free.

30:33.415 --> 30:34.917
Are you okay?

30:36.001 --> 30:38.087
Set them free!
[ Gasps, groans ]

30:39.463 --> 30:41.715
Hey, go sit in the car.

30:41.757 --> 30:44.093
[ Dogs barking ]

30:54.103 --> 30:56.689
[ Machinery whirring,
metal grinding ]

30:58.482 --> 31:00.526
Hello! Mr. Garrison?!

31:00.568 --> 31:02.570
Hello?!

31:02.611 --> 31:04.363
[ Machine powering down ]

31:04.405 --> 31:07.283
Garrison: There those
adventurers are!

31:07.324 --> 31:10.578
Oh, yes, yes.
Come here. Come here.

31:10.619 --> 31:11.870
Oh, you good boys.

31:11.912 --> 31:13.706
Detective Jared Vasquez
with NYPD.

31:13.747 --> 31:17.668
Oh, thank you, Detective.
Aren't you glad to see me, huh?

31:20.421 --> 31:22.089
Set them free.

31:22.131 --> 31:27.678
♪♪

31:27.720 --> 31:30.973
Woman: Flight 828 now boarding.
Flight 828.

31:31.015 --> 31:33.225
All things
work together for good.

31:39.732 --> 31:42.109
[ Hinges creak ]

31:42.151 --> 31:44.028
Listen, Mr. Garrison.
I have to disclose

31:44.069 --> 31:46.238
that we're aware of who
broke open your gate.

31:46.280 --> 31:48.324
-Are ya, now?
-Yeah.

31:48.365 --> 31:51.285
They're two people who
have just been through a
hell of a crisis, sir.

31:51.327 --> 31:53.203
I'd consider it a favor
if you'd be willing

31:53.245 --> 31:55.914
to, uh, forgo
pressing charges.

31:55.956 --> 31:57.583
Of course, I'll pay
for all the repairs.

31:57.625 --> 32:00.711
Not a problem. I'm not looking
to put anyone behind bars.

32:00.753 --> 32:04.840
♪♪

32:04.882 --> 32:07.343
Set them free.
Set them free!

32:08.719 --> 32:11.472
Set them free.
Set them free.

32:11.513 --> 32:15.559
♪♪

32:15.601 --> 32:18.228
Set! Them! Free!
Set them free.

32:23.859 --> 32:26.945
Set them free.

32:26.987 --> 32:30.074
Set them free.

32:30.115 --> 32:32.242
Set them free.

32:32.284 --> 32:40.376
♪♪

32:40.417 --> 32:48.509
♪♪

32:48.550 --> 32:50.719
-What the hell are you doing?!
-Michaela! Stop!

32:52.221 --> 32:53.681
Michaela!

32:57.309 --> 33:00.437
[ Children sobbing ]

33:00.479 --> 33:01.814
Jared!

33:04.233 --> 33:06.402
[ Handcuffs click ]

33:06.443 --> 33:08.737
[ Children sobbing, bar clangs ]

33:08.779 --> 33:11.615
It's okay. It's okay.
You're going home.

33:11.657 --> 33:13.867
It's okay. It's done.
It's all over.

33:13.909 --> 33:17.287
Are you guys okay?
Are you okay?

33:17.329 --> 33:19.665
Okay.
[ Breathing heavily ]

33:24.878 --> 33:26.463
[ Siren wails ]

33:26.505 --> 33:29.425
[ Camera shutter clicks,
police radio chatter ]

33:29.466 --> 33:32.177
[ Indistinct conversations ]

33:36.140 --> 33:38.016
Officer.

33:38.058 --> 33:40.310
Captain.
Long time no see.

33:40.352 --> 33:42.271
For you, at least.

33:42.312 --> 33:44.481
Sounds like congratulations
are in order.

33:44.523 --> 33:46.316
According to Vasquez,
this was all you.

33:47.401 --> 33:48.736
I'm happy to help.

33:48.777 --> 33:51.780
Take a few days off,
clear your head,

33:51.822 --> 33:53.323
then come in,
and we'll talk.

33:53.365 --> 33:55.284
See if we can figure out
getting you back on the beat.

33:55.325 --> 33:57.411
Thank you.

33:57.453 --> 34:00.372
Those girls are alive
because you came back.

34:00.414 --> 34:02.332
It's lucky for all of us.

34:02.374 --> 34:04.960
[ Radio chatter continues ]

34:14.595 --> 34:16.472
Thanks for putting in
a good word.

34:17.890 --> 34:20.392
It's the least I can do.

34:24.480 --> 34:27.232
So, I suppose you're
not gonna explain to me
what happened here today.

34:28.692 --> 34:32.279
Like I said,
I wish I could. I...

34:32.321 --> 34:36.408
♪♪

34:36.450 --> 34:39.244
You still
take my breath away.

34:39.286 --> 34:43.832
♪♪

34:43.874 --> 34:46.001
Say hi to Lourdes
for me.

34:46.043 --> 34:55.093
♪♪

34:55.135 --> 34:57.888
[ Cellphone rings,
stops abruptly ]

35:04.061 --> 35:06.146
You okay?

35:06.188 --> 35:07.773
Yeah.

35:07.815 --> 35:11.235
Usually you're the optimist.
I'm doom and gloom, remember?

35:11.276 --> 35:13.695
I am optimistic.

35:13.737 --> 35:15.739
And so grateful.

35:15.781 --> 35:19.451
Said the woman looking like
she's about to toss her cookies.

35:19.493 --> 35:21.870
[ Chuckles softly ]

35:21.912 --> 35:25.040
I have so much
to apologize to you for.

35:27.459 --> 35:29.419
We don't have to
get into this now.

35:29.461 --> 35:31.547
No, I know. I just...

35:37.970 --> 35:43.141
I have spent every day of
the last five years blaming you.

35:44.434 --> 35:46.353
Not only for taking
that later flight,

35:46.395 --> 35:49.356
but for making Cal so desperate
for your attention

35:49.398 --> 35:51.567
that he wanted
to stay with you.

35:51.608 --> 35:57.072
I had maybe, what,
six months left with him?

35:57.114 --> 35:59.575
And even that
you took away from me.

36:01.076 --> 36:03.078
But the thing is...

36:03.120 --> 36:07.291
I realize now that...

36:07.332 --> 36:10.335
for Cal to be here
with us today...

36:12.671 --> 36:15.465
...for Olive to have
her twin alive,

36:15.507 --> 36:19.303
to maybe grow up
beside her...

36:19.344 --> 36:23.181
Cal had to be
on that plane.

36:23.223 --> 36:24.850
He had to.

36:24.892 --> 36:29.187
♪♪

36:29.229 --> 36:32.316
Oh, what you've both
been through.

36:34.651 --> 36:37.070
The only reason we were
on that trip in the first place

36:37.112 --> 36:40.157
was because
you insisted...

36:40.198 --> 36:41.783
and bribed me with sex.

36:41.825 --> 36:43.493
[ Chuckles ]

36:43.535 --> 36:45.871
[ Sniffles ]

36:47.331 --> 36:50.667
So if anyone saved Cal...

36:50.709 --> 36:53.295
I'm pretty sure
it was you.

36:54.630 --> 36:57.257
No.

36:57.299 --> 37:00.427
This is
bigger than us.

37:02.554 --> 37:05.307
[ Video game playing ]

37:05.349 --> 37:13.106
♪♪

37:13.148 --> 37:20.864
♪♪

37:20.906 --> 37:28.664
♪♪

37:28.705 --> 37:31.708
Copy.
Everything checks out.

37:31.750 --> 37:34.628
Then tomorrow, we take it
apart piece by piece.

37:34.670 --> 37:36.672
This isn't close to over.

37:38.882 --> 37:40.050
Man on TV:
Williams into the front court.

37:40.092 --> 37:42.344
Dumps it off left side.
Peel!

37:42.386 --> 37:44.680
How are you so fast?

37:44.721 --> 37:47.975
-Dump.
-Finished.

37:48.016 --> 37:49.893
-Oh, come on.
-That's ridiculous.

37:49.935 --> 37:52.187
-Cal! Amazing!
-You just learned how to play.

37:52.229 --> 37:53.814
Ben:
[ Laughs ] Nice.

37:53.855 --> 37:56.733
Well, not bad for the tiniest
15-year-old on --

37:58.360 --> 38:00.737
Ben?
Are you all right?

38:00.779 --> 38:03.824
Yeah, I just got dizzy
for a second.

38:03.865 --> 38:05.742
I'm fine, really.
Don't worry.

38:05.784 --> 38:07.703
Everything's great.

38:07.744 --> 38:09.454
Drink some water.
I'll get more snacks.

38:09.496 --> 38:11.498
Woman on TV: ...NBC4 update.

38:11.540 --> 38:14.334
Sisters Hallie
and Samantha Pyler
have been rescued.

38:14.376 --> 38:16.253
The kidnapped sisters
were found safe

38:16.294 --> 38:18.046
at an Astoria metal shop

38:18.088 --> 38:20.590
and are being treated
at the scene.

38:20.632 --> 38:22.676
[ Cellphone buzzes ]

38:22.718 --> 38:31.018
♪♪

38:31.059 --> 38:34.479
[ Keyboard clicking ]

38:42.571 --> 38:48.744
♪♪

38:48.785 --> 38:51.079
[ Whispers ]
What are you gonna do?

38:51.121 --> 38:58.628
♪♪

38:58.670 --> 39:06.136
♪♪

39:06.178 --> 39:13.685
♪♪

39:13.727 --> 39:16.229
[ Door opens ]

39:16.271 --> 39:19.483
Welcome home.
Ears burning much?

39:19.524 --> 39:22.778
You're the subject
of my sermon this Sunday.

39:24.237 --> 39:27.824
How do we know
if we're the called?

39:29.868 --> 39:31.661
We know in our heart.

39:36.958 --> 39:40.128
You okay? Michaela?

39:43.006 --> 39:44.341
Can I take this?

39:45.884 --> 39:47.844
As long as you put it
to good use.

39:50.138 --> 39:51.389
Looks like
your ride's here.

39:51.431 --> 39:52.766
[ Door closes ]

39:52.808 --> 40:02.400
♪♪

40:02.442 --> 40:04.277
You saved those girls.

40:04.319 --> 40:06.488
We saved those girls.

40:07.614 --> 40:10.033
How'd you know
I was here?

40:12.661 --> 40:15.205
I just...knew.

40:17.457 --> 40:19.501
What is this?

40:19.543 --> 40:21.878
What is happening?

40:21.920 --> 40:24.631
How about this? There were a lot
of people on that plane.

40:24.673 --> 40:28.176
Why you and me? What makes two
head cases like us so special?

40:29.511 --> 40:32.180
What's the probability
it's just you and me?

40:32.222 --> 40:36.560
♪♪

40:36.601 --> 40:38.145
Michaela:
And, of course, it wasn't

40:38.186 --> 40:39.479
just the two of us.

40:39.521 --> 40:42.899
♪♪

40:42.941 --> 40:47.654
[ Violin playing ]

40:47.696 --> 40:51.825
[ Music stops ]

40:51.867 --> 40:54.536
[ Television playing ]

40:54.578 --> 41:00.959
♪♪

41:01.001 --> 41:07.424
♪♪

41:07.465 --> 41:13.847
♪♪

41:13.889 --> 41:17.434
Ben and I didn't know
any of these people yet.

41:17.475 --> 41:21.938
♪♪

41:21.980 --> 41:24.357
But soon, we'd know them
as well as we know ourselves.

41:24.399 --> 41:28.612
♪♪

41:28.653 --> 41:31.948
As for whatever force
brought us all here...

41:36.786 --> 41:39.623
...it had no interest
in being investigated.

41:39.664 --> 41:45.670
♪♪

41:45.712 --> 41:50.634
And as for the group of us?

41:50.675 --> 41:53.011
This was just the beginning.

41:55.472 --> 42:02.687
♪♪

42:02.729 --> 42:09.945
♪♪

42:09.986 --> 42:17.202
♪♪

42:17.244 --> 42:25.418
♪♪
